  "usageNotes": {
    "teacherGuidance": "Start with real objects to make equal groups. Use pencils, blocks, or counters. Let students physically create groups before moving to written multiplication.",
    "parentGuidance": "Help your child see equal groups at home. Arrange biscuits on plates equally, put shoes in pairs, or stack books in equal piles.",
    "studentGuidance": "Multiplication is just making equal groups! When you put the same number of things in each group and count the total, you are multiplying!"
